text: The Sullivan and Richie Jean Jackson House, at 1416 Lapsley Ave. in Selma, Alabama, was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2014. It is a one-story wood frame bungalow which was built in 1906 and was remodeled around 1960. It has wide-board siding and a metal pyramid roof, and is built upon a brick and concrete foundation. With accompanying 25 photos from 2012. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Dallas County, Alabama Category:Buildings and structures in Alabama
